Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and finely chop @carrot{3%ounce}. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

While cavatappi cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add carrot; cook, stirring, until browned and tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Increase heat under pan with carrot to medium high and add a drizzle of oil. Push carrot to one side of pan.

Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} to empty side. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4-6%minutes}. Sprinkle with @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until beef is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season generously with salt and pepper.

> Swap in sausage for beef. (Skip adding salt and pepper.)

Stir carrot and beef to combine.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Stir in @marinara{1%14oz cup} and @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} until combined.

Divide pasta between #plates or bowls{}. Top with @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} and remaining chopped parsley. Serve with @?butter{1%tablespoon} if desired.